Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.16,0:01:02.59,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Hello, everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.73,0:01:05.36,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Hello. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.43,0:01:11.13,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.17,0:01:13.20,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.27,0:01:15.57,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.64,0:01:18.21,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Hello, everybody. Welcome to the Grand Tour,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.27,0:01:21.14,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,which, this week, comes from the Netherlands.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.85,0:01:26.88,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,We're setting something of a record, actually,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.95,0:01:32.15,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,cos we are the first three British men ever to come here for a weekend
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.15,0:01:34.16,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,and not vomit on a prostitute.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.49,0:01:37.23,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Actually, we love coming to Holland.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.29,0:01:38.96,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,James for his... for his own reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.26,0:01:44.00,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,And I like it because the Dutch are officially
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.07,0:01:46.17,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,the tallest people on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.17,0:01:47.90,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,It's true. True fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.97,0:01:50.51,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-Yes, and I hate it here. I'm sick of...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.57,0:01:53.51,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm sick of staring at belly buttons all day.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.58,0:01:58.95,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,The only problem I do have here is that I'm not allowed to use the word "swaffelen".
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.42,0:02:01.92,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, you just did, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.98,0:02:06.19,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,No, the thing is, OK, it is a really bad word here,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.25,0:02:07.86,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,and I have no idea why.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.92,0:02:10.63,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-What does it mean? -It means...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.86,0:02:15.70,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,It means to bang your gentleman sausage...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.76,0:02:17.93,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,...on the side of the Taj Mahal.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.00,0:02:19.93,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-Oh, God!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.00,0:02:21.74,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Anyway, listen. Erm...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.80,0:02:25.47,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,We're in Rotterdam, which is a marvellous city, in fact,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.54,0:02:27.61,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,because you aren't allowed to bring a car into the city -
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.68,0:02:32.25,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,a petrol car - if it was built before 1992.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.31,0:02:36.62,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,You aren't allowed to bring a diesel car into the city if it was built before 2000,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.68,0:02:40.05,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,which means you're never held up by poor people.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.06,0:02:45.93,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-Really? -What else can we say about the Dutch?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.99,0:02:48.73,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-Oh, of course, you gave the world speed cameras. -Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.80,0:02:51.73,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-So thank you very much for that. -Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.80,0:02:53.97,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,No, actually, I'd far rather be pulled over
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.04,0:02:57.54,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,by the actual Dutch police rather than a speed camera,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.61,0:03:00.24,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,cos, boy, oh, boy, do these guys look good.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.31,0:03:01.31,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-We've got a picture here. -Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.28,0:03:07.85,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I would very much like to see a lady policeman in an outfit like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.92,0:03:11.02,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-It looks like the guy on the right already has.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.09,0:03:13.92,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-Shall we get on with the show... man?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.99,0:03:15.59,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes, good idea. Er...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.66,0:03:18.86,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,And coming up in our programme about cars this week...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.16,0:03:22.03,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I try to pull a camel.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.10,0:03:24.40,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Come on. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.47,0:03:26.63,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,A donkey pulls James.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.90,0:03:30.44,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,And Richard gets stuck in a cow orgy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.51,0:03:33.74,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I-I really am alarmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.81,0:03:39.35,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,But first, there's been a bit of an argument in the office between these two.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.41,0:03:41.18,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,You see, Richard maintains
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.28,0:03:45.85,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,that the Mazda MX-5 is all the sports car you would ever need.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.92,0:03:49.19,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-Because it is. -Mm-hm. But James says it isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.29,0:03:50.79,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Because it isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.13,0:03:54.80,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,So we decided they should sort it out
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.86,0:03:59.40,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,by going to the obvious proving ground for all sports cars:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.47,0:04:01.40,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,North Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.97,0:04:38.67,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,RICHARD: This is it,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.74,0:04:43.35,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,the latest version of the bestselling two-seater roadster of all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.51,0:04:46.45,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,And it's easy to see why.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.51,0:04:48.05,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Peppy little engine at the front,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.12,0:04:51.42,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,two seats in the open air in the middle, rearwheel drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.49,0:04:54.09,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,It's the perfect sports-car recipe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.16,0:04:56.96,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,But layered on top of that in this new version
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.02,0:04:59.43,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,you get air conditioning, heated seats,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.49,0:05:01.83,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,lane-departure assist, cruise control,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.90,0:05:04.63,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,rain-sensing wipers, dusk-sensing headlamps.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.70,0:05:06.83,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,You just can't do any better.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.90,0:05:10.74,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, you can, actually, because all of those luxury items you're mentioning now,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.81,0:05:14.48,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,they just add weight, and they mean it isn't a true sports car any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.54,0:05:15.98,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-Yes, it is. -No, it isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.04,0:05:18.75,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Colin Chapman, he was the bloke who founded Lotus,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.81,0:05:22.78,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,he said the ethos of a sports car is simplify and add lightness.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.85,0:05:25.62,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,He didn't say you simplify and add electric windows.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.69,0:05:30.19,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Yep, and then he gave all his money away to a drug dealer called John DeLorean.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.26,0:05:32.13,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,This, ladies and gentlemen, is what it's actually about.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.19,0:05:34.20,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,This is called the Zenos.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.26,0:05:37.90,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,You get four wheels, you get somewhere to sit, an engine, and that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.97,0:05:39.50,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,It's a sports car.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.57,0:05:42.64,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-Yeah. What do you do if it rains? -Well, you'd get wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.70,0:05:44.64,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,What if you want to listen to the radio?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.71,0:05:46.57,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Why would I want to listen to the radio around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.64,0:05:48.28,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-Does it have a heater? -No.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.41,0:05:51.18,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-Has it got windows? -Look, if you buy a football boot,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.25,0:05:54.28,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,you don't expect it to be usable as a ballet shoe, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.42,0:05:59.19,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,But Mazda has invented a football boot that you can wear to the opera.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.25,0:06:03.02,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Look, I can guarantee that if you wear that shoe to the opera house...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.09,0:06:04.86,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,RICHARD: At this point, the director said
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.93,0:06:07.90,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,he'd heard enough about shoes for one day...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.13,0:06:13.64,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,...and told us to go for a drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.24,0:06:24.18,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Right, now I'm away from Hammond's luxury sports car resort,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.25,0:06:27.45,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,let me tell you a little bit about this remarkable car.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.72,0:06:31.12,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,It's powered by the 2L turbocharged engine
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.19,0:06:34.72,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,from the Ford Focus ST, giving 250 horsepower.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.79,0:06:37.46,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,That's mounted in the middle, right behind my head there,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.49,0:06:39.83,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,driving the rear wheels through a no-nonsense,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.89,0:06:43.16,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,old-school six-speed gearbox.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.23,0:06:46.77,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Now, 250 horsepower doesn't sound like a huge amount in the modern world,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.83,0:06:49.84,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,but this car, made with an aluminium spine
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.90,0:06:52.71,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,and composite tub, and all the rest of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.77,0:06:54.74,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,weighs less than three quarters of a tonne,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.81,0:06:57.04,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,so it is genuinely quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.11,0:06:58.78,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Look... Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.83,0:07:16.73,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,It makes the noise of some futuristic propulsion system powered by antimatter.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.17,0:07:24.14,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes! Electrifying!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.15,0:07:36.15,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,James comes from a world where he wants his phone and his camera separate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.22,0:07:37.72,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,"I like a paper diary."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.79,0:07:40.86,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,This Mazda is a smartphone. It does everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.33,0:07:48.06,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,It looks brilliant, it will be endlessly reliable, it's fast,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.13,0:07:51.03,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,it's got speakers in the headrests, and it handles well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.20,0:07:58.57,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,And you can get an MX-5 from ?18,500.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.64,0:08:01.54,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,James's car starts at ?33,000,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.54,0:08:03.78,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,and you don't even get doors!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.85,0:08:06.21,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,My shed has got doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.28,0:08:09.05,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I furnish my cats with doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.12,0:08:10.65,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,You need doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.03,0:08:21.40,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I bet he's being shaken to death in that thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.46,0:08:23.20,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I bet Hammond thinks I'm being shaken to death in here,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.26,0:08:24.60,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,but actually he's wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.67,0:08:28.04,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,because this isn't like a BAC Mono or a Radical.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.10,0:08:31.44,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,It is obviously very much a car for taking on the track,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.57,0:08:33.37,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,but it's been tuned for road use.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.44,0:08:34.64,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,It's quite supple.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.71,0:08:35.81,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,See? Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.88,0:08:38.41,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Bump. It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.48,0:08:39.88,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm very relaxed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.45,0:08:48.02,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,JAMES: Eventually, we pulled over for a cup of coffee
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.09,0:08:50.26,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,and a bit more arguing about doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.89,0:08:54.06,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Just because they had them in the 12th century
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.13,0:08:56.40,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,on cathedrals, whatever, you don't need them now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.46,0:08:57.87,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Don't be a slave to convention.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.93,0:09:00.00,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,But people had eyelids in the 12th century,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.07,0:09:02.70,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,and nobody's deciding, "Let's get rid of those, they're old hat."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.77,0:09:05.21,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,"Oh, no! I've got dust in my eyes and I can't sleep."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.27,0:09:07.41,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,That's completely facile, Hammond. You know exactly what I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.47,0:09:10.08,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,The door... I mean, Riva speedboats don't have doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.14,0:09:11.61,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,You don't say...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.65,0:09:14.48,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,This is lovely, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.62,0:09:16.08,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.15,0:09:18.72,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, word reached me that you two were talking rubbish.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.79,0:09:22.22,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-What do you mean, "rubbish"? -Well, if you want the best sports car,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.29,0:09:24.83,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,you don't want a Mazda or a Zenos. You want--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.89,0:09:26.73,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, God. He's brought an Alfa Romeo.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.79,0:09:28.30,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes, of course I have.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.36,0:09:31.30,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Alfa Romeo 4C Spider.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.37,0:09:40.64,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,JEREMY: This is what I'm talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.64,0:09:43.48,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,A symphony in carbon fibre.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.54,0:09:45.51,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Balance personified.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.65,0:09:47.95,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,The Graduate updated.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.02,0:09:50.92,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,A mini Ferrari, as cute as a bunny rabbit,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.99,0:09:54.39,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,with the greatest badge in the history of mo--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.46,0:09:56.12,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,How much is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.19,0:09:59.66,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-You know perfectly well how much it is. -Yeah, we've forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.29,0:10:01.83,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Money is vulgar.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.90,0:10:06.07,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,You can't put a price on something as exquisite as that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.13,0:10:08.34,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but Alfa Romeo did put a price on it, didn't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.40,0:10:09.47,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,And what was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.54,0:10:11.67,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-Sixty thousand pounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.74,0:10:15.14,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,So you could have both of our cars and everything in the back of shot
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.21,0:10:17.28,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,for the price of one of these Alfa Romeos?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.34,0:10:20.72,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I know, it is extraordinary value for money.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.78,0:10:24.29,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-It's too far from outside to inside. -It's miles!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.35,0:10:25.75,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,JEREMY: Yes, thick sills...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.82,0:10:27.69,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-Here we go. -...for strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.76,0:10:29.96,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Look at this, rotary heater knobs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.02,0:10:32.49,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-It's like being in the 1970s. -Yeah, it is, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.56,0:10:33.80,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,This handbrake, look at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.86,0:10:36.03,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Is that fixed on or does that come off?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.10,0:10:38.53,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Alfa Romeo, purveyors of disappointment for nearly three decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.60,0:10:40.60,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,RICHARD: Look at this. Classy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.67,0:10:43.24,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,RICHARD: Yeah. Feel the quality in that. JAMES: Let me feel that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.30,0:10:46.11,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,RICHARD: Mm. JAMES: Sixty thousand pounds?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.17,0:10:47.41,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,RICHARD: Mm. And this...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.47,0:10:49.08,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,That's what you want to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.14,0:10:51.98,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,If you ever buy a new item of clothing, never show it these two.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.05,0:10:56.15,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,"What are you wearing that jacket for? It makes you look like a German gameshow host."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.22,0:10:57.89,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,RICHARD: That's satisfying.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.95,0:10:59.75,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,JAMES: Why are you wearing that jacket?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.82,0:11:01.99,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Because I was at a party in India last night,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.06,0:11:03.46,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,and I've hurried over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.52,0:11:04.99,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,RICHARD: Why did you go to the party
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.06,0:11:06.33,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,dressed as a German gameshow host?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.26,0:11:10.73,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,JEREMY: Soon, I grew weary of their abuse
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.80,0:11:13.33,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,and set off in what, be in no doubt,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.40,0:11:17.54,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,is my favourite car on sale today.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.60,0:11:23.61,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I will admit, there are one or two tiny little problems with the 4C.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.75,0:11:25.21,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Trivial stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.28,0:11:29.15,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,It's very wide. The gearbox is a little bit dim-witted.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.22,0:11:33.59,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,If you fit sports exhausts, the noise is catastrophic.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.65,0:11:36.02,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,The petrol tank... yeah, that's too small.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.09,0:11:40.76,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,You've really only got a range of 300... yards.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.80,0:11:42.96,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,And then there's the steering.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.03,0:11:46.67,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,There's no power assistance, so it's incredibly heavy when you're parking,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.77,0:11:49.77,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,there's no feel when you're on the move.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.84,0:11:51.54,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,And then, and this is its party piece,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.61,0:11:57.14,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,just occasionally, it'll go violently left or right for no reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.01,0:12:00.28,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Whoa! You see that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.35,0:12:01.42,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Bloody hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.02,0:12:09.79,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,But look at it this way, we could all probably find fault with our children,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.82,0:12:12.46,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,and yet... we still love them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.26,0:12:18.87,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,RICHARD: Jeremy loves Alfa Romeos
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.93,0:12:20.33,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,because, back in the old days,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.40,0:12:23.10,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,they were great... but they're not any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.54,0:12:27.01,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Plenty of things were great.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.07,0:12:28.54,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Greece.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.61,0:12:30.01,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Rolf Harris.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.98,0:12:32.48,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,You can't love them now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.15,0:12:39.05,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Another small problem with the Alfa
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.12,0:12:40.42,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,that I didn't mention earlier
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.49,0:12:42.62,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,is that you get cramp after five minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.83,0:12:48.83,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna have to stop and go for a walk,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.90,0:12:50.43,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,and they'll want to know why,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.50,0:12:53.50,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,and I'll have to tell them I need a wee or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.57,0:12:54.97,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,No, diarrhoea.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.04,0:12:57.40,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Sorry, I've got to stop. I've got to stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.47,0:13:00.71,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,RADIO: I'm just stopping for a minute here. Hang on.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.84,0:13:02.24,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Why are you stopping for a minute?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.41,0:13:05.21,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,JEREMY: Ohhh! Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.28,0:13:06.85,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, why are you hopping about?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.88,0:13:09.68,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Look at the snowy mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.75,0:13:11.45,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,You are welcome to Morocco.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.52,0:13:14.66,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Ah, merci, monsieur. Comment ca va?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.72,0:13:16.19,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,JAMES: God above.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.06,0:13:19.66,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-Have you got cramp? -No.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.73,0:13:21.23,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes, you have.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.30,0:13:24.17,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Right, good. Well, I've seen the view.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.23,0:13:27.23,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to see the view, and it's lovely.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.74,0:13:35.88,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,JEREMY: Back on the road, James suddenly delivered
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.88,0:13:39.15,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,a very un-James-manlike observation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.21,0:13:42.55,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,My car is seriously quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.62,0:13:44.15,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,It's not as fast as this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.99,0:13:46.32,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I bet it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.39,0:13:52.53,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,James, this has a turbocharged 1750cc engine
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.59,0:13:54.03,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,from a Fiat Punto.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.10,0:13:58.00,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Mine's 2L with a twin-scroll turbocharger.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.07,0:14:03.14,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Have you noticed Hammond is being strangely quiet on the subject of speed?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.20,0:14:06.01,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, just listening to you two bicker.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.07,0:14:09.11,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I am a bit down on power, if I'm honest.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.18,0:14:15.15,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I think Hammond's in a sort of retirement home for former distressed sports-car owners.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.69,0:14:21.69,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,JEREMY:  Right, next straight bit of road, James May,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.76,0:14:26.03,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I will pull over and show you what real speed is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.56,0:14:29.40,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-Cows.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.46,0:14:32.00,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,RICHARD:  On a roof rack. I've never seen that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.47,0:14:38.27,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,JEREMY: Soon, we found a suitable stretch of road...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.34,0:14:41.08,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,...and Hammond agreed to be the starter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.48,0:14:46.61,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-I've got launch control. -Not interested.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.02,0:14:51.75,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,JEREMY: Are you ready? Before anyone comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.82,0:14:54.99,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,RICHARD: In three, two, one, go!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.76,0:15:02.60,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, now, that's just impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.20,0:15:09.20,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,It's the Zenos...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.27,0:15:11.67,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,which means James May has just won a drag race.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.51,0:15:18.01,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,JEREMY: But for me, that wasn't the biggest surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.08,0:15:21.32,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I don't understand why this lost,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.38,0:15:23.99,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,because instead of a conventional chassis,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.02,0:15:26.12,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,it has a carbon-fibre tub,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.19,0:15:28.89,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,like you get in a Formula One car
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.99,0:15:30.99,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,or a McLaren P1.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.99,0:15:37.66,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,And a carbon-fibre tub makes a car... expensive, but light.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.73,0:15:39.83,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Very light.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.90,0:15:42.60,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm trying to work out why I lost that race.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.67,0:15:45.87,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I think it's cos your car isn't as fast as mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.01,0:15:47.17,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,RICHARD: That was a factor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.24,0:15:50.04,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but mine is so light.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.11,0:15:51.38,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,RICHARD: How do you know it's light?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.45,0:15:52.41,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Every time Alfa say how much it weighs,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.48,0:15:54.25,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,they give a different figure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.32,0:15:56.05,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,JEREMY: Yeah, that's because they've got
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.12,0:15:59.65,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,better things to do than go around weighing cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.72,0:16:01.79,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,When Picasso had finished one of his paintings,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.86,0:16:04.83,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,he didn't say, "Oh, I wonder how much that weighs."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.89,0:16:08.13,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,You need to know the weight of an Alfa for when you resell it,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.20,0:16:10.73,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,because you buy scrap cars by weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.43,0:16:14.80,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,JEREMY: With the Zenos, that was built in Norfolk,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.87,0:16:16.90,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,so obviously they're gonna weigh it - there's nothing else to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.04,0:16:19.04,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,This is from Milan.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.07,0:16:23.14,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,They finished making it, and then they went into town with one and pulled girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.35,0:16:26.81,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,JAMES:  It's massive and it's made of pig iron,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.88,0:16:28.12,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,that's the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.18,0:16:30.12,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I can see the carbon fibre...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.18,0:16:34.26,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,JEREMY: The weight argument raged on for the rest of the journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.92,0:16:38.56,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,So, that night, at the hotel,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.63,0:16:40.46,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I came up with a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.53,0:16:43.06,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna weigh all three cars
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.06,0:16:46.87,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,to prove the Alfa's the lightest.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.93,0:16:50.17,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,The problem with your plan is that you'd need a weighbridge, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.24,0:16:51.54,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-Yes. -Well, hang on.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.61,0:16:53.37,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-Well, get one. -No, there isn't one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.44,0:16:55.71,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I have got the hotel brochure here, actually,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.78,0:16:58.61,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,and, do you know, it's got three restaurants,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.68,0:17:03.45,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,a spa, and a gym, a business centre, tennis court.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.52,0:17:04.92,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,JEREMY: Mm-hm. -But with one glaring omission.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.99,0:17:06.79,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-What? -There's no weighbridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.85,0:17:10.19,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-No! -They haven't thought of that. I'd knock a star off.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.13,0:17:13.26,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I shall build one.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.33,0:17:16.10,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I shall build a weighbridge, and then you shall see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.53,0:17:22.70,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-I will build a weighbridge. -That could have been
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.77,0:17:27.91,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,a really useful and interesting test, and you've ruined it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.97,0:17:29.98,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,People are interested in Alfa Romeos!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.11,0:17:32.71,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,People are interested in murders, they don't want to see one.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.78,0:17:35.82,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Anyway, anyway, we'll have more of that later on,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.88,0:17:38.95,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,but first, it is now time for us to engage reverse
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.02,0:17:43.22,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,and park neatly in a marked space on Conversation Street.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.13,0:17:56.60,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Right, now, which nation on earth has the worst police cars?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.67,0:17:59.74,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's some good conversation. I like that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.81,0:18:02.74,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,The worst police cars, it's definitely not the Americans, is it,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.81,0:18:05.28,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,because they have those Crown Vics, and they're rearwheel drive V8s.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.35,0:18:09.52,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-That's what you need. -They're good police cars. Not the Americans.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.58,0:18:12.99,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-Erm... -It's us. It's the British.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.05,0:18:16.62,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah. We have those dreary little Vauxhall diesel Astras.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.69,0:18:18.06,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Opels if you live here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.16,0:18:20.73,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Or, if you're in America, those miserable little Chevrolets
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.79,0:18:22.53,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,that are actually Daewoos. It's awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.60,0:18:24.27,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Most countries around the world
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.33,0:18:26.67,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,would traditionally have always had a police car that was made there,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.73,0:18:28.57,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,one of their own cars. Wouldn't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.64,0:18:30.37,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,And the funny thing is, that's not what they used to do here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.44,0:18:31.41,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-In Holland? -No.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.47,0:18:33.34,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,You don't surprise me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.41,0:18:37.81,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,What they actually had for many years, about 30 years, was Porsches.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.88,0:18:40.85,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-What? -The police used Porsches, yeah. Remember? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.91,0:18:43.42,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-Do you know, I'd forgotten. You're right, they did. -They did.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.48,0:18:45.49,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,How did they persuade the government?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.55,0:18:48.02,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,It's masterful. It's genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.09,0:18:49.62,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Absolute respect to everybody who did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.69,0:18:52.29,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,What they did was say, "Right, we need...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.36,0:18:53.93,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Hm. I think we need a Porsche
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.99,0:18:57.00,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,because it's air-cooled and the engine is at the back,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.06,0:19:01.07,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,and that would be handy if we have to reverse at high speed for a long time."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.20,0:19:02.34,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,They actually said that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.40,0:19:03.77,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,They did. And this gets better.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.84,0:19:06.24,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,And I'm not making this up. They did say this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.31,0:19:08.28,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,They need a car where you can remove the roof
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.34,0:19:12.38,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,so you can stand on the seats to address traffic in an emergency situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.45,0:19:15.28,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,So what they need is a 911 Targa,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.35,0:19:17.85,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,and matching sunglasses, I presume, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.92,0:19:20.75,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Did they also say, "And it comes with 911 on the back
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.82,0:19:22.62,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,which is our telephone number"?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.69,0:19:25.26,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,The thing is, it doesn't, and they're still at it,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.33,0:19:27.79,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,because the cycle cops around here,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.86,0:19:29.03,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,and there's a lot of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.10,0:19:30.63,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,they managed to persuade the government
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.70,0:19:34.00,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,that they need mountain bikes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.07,0:19:35.70,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-What, here? -In Holland.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.77,0:19:38.41,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,It's the flattest country on earth
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.47,0:19:40.37,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,and they need mountain bikes!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.44,0:19:42.58,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,"Yes, I might see a mountain." What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.81,0:19:44.91,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,The best thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.98,0:19:52.45,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,The best thing is, it gives us an opportunity to have one more look
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.52,0:19:56.06,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,at a photograph of the Dutch mountain cop police.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.12,0:19:58.56,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-There they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.63,0:20:00.69,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-Now, I want to talk about otters.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.76,0:20:02.46,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-What? -I want to talk about otters.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.53,0:20:04.63,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,You see, a few years ago somebody in Holland
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.70,0:20:09.47,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,worked out that there were only 185 otters in the entire country.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.54,0:20:11.04,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Jeremy, it's a car show.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.10,0:20:13.71,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Bear with me, OK, because I've got the figures here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.77,0:20:18.55,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,In 2014, 21 of these otters were run over.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.61,0:20:23.25,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,OK? In 2015, 49 were run over.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.32,0:20:26.55,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,You only have 185 otters in the whole country,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.62,0:20:31.86,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,and in two years, you've flattened 70 of them under your cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.93,0:20:34.33,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-What is your problem with otters?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.40,0:20:36.66,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,The thing is that I don't want people to get the wrong impression.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.73,0:20:40.40,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I don't want everyone to think that Dutch people go around murdering animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.47,0:20:41.77,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Let me explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.84,0:20:46.17,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Recently, the government here spent 150,000 euros,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.24,0:20:48.21,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,and that's ?150,000,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.28,0:20:50.28,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,?160,000, ?170,000...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.34,0:20:52.05,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-That's Brexit for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.11,0:20:56.65,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,We can't even afford to put mayonnaise on our chips now any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.72,0:21:01.99,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Er... Anyway, they spent 150,000 euros on a bridge over a road
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.06,0:21:03.72,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,so squirrels could cross safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.79,0:21:06.39,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,We've got a picture of the bridge. It's a substantial thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.46,0:21:08.13,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,You know this bridge? A famous bridge?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.19,0:21:11.10,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-That's a squirrel bridge? -Yeah, it's a squirrel bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.16,0:21:14.90,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Anyway, how many squirrels do you think have used it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.14,0:21:17.80,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,A squillion.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.87,0:21:20.97,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I see where you're going with that one, James. No, it isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.04,0:21:22.14,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I've got the figures here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.21,0:21:25.45,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,"CCTV footage has revealed, in 2014,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.51,0:21:27.55,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,three squirrels used it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.61,0:21:31.35,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,In 2015, it was used only twice."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.42,0:21:35.66,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, why didn't the third squirrel use it again in 2015?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.72,0:21:37.92,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-It probably got run over. -Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.99,0:21:40.79,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,By somebody mistaking him for an otter.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.86,0:21:42.03,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Get it! Get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.10,0:21:48.50,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,You've probably read the other day, the Dutch are taking a view
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.57,0:21:50.67,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,on whether to allow people to...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.01,0:21:54.41,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,How can I put this? Assisted dying of somebody -
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.48,0:21:57.74,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,feels as though their life is complete, OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.81,0:21:59.78,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,This is something that occupies me a lot,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.85,0:22:02.68,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I'll be honest with you, because I sometimes think...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.75,0:22:05.15,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,"Oh, have I done enough now?"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.22,0:22:06.85,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,OTHERS: Yes. -No.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.05,0:22:09.39,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,No, you know, when?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.46,0:22:11.19,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,When would it be appropriate for me to think,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.26,0:22:12.99,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,"Time to end."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.06,0:22:14.93,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,OTHERS: Now. -No.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.00,0:22:19.13,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-May I get on with it? -Yeah, do. Do it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.20,0:22:21.97,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,No, what I want to say is, OK...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.04,0:22:23.57,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I'll get the forms, there can't be many.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.64,0:22:25.21,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,The time comes... Ssh!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.27,0:22:28.88,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,The time, I think, comes when you stop wanting to be an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.94,0:22:30.64,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,That's the time when you've done enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.71,0:22:32.68,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,- I know what you mean. - No, actually, you are right,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.75,0:22:35.25,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,cos I think it's the moment where you go into a big department store,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.32,0:22:39.25,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,and you go into the kitchenware section, and you see a tea cosy,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.32,0:22:40.79,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,but you don't put it on your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.85,0:22:42.72,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.79,0:22:45.76,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Not putting things on your head is a sign it's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.83,0:22:48.50,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,And the time you don't want to put gloves on your ears
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.56,0:22:50.43,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,and pretend to be a reindeer.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.50,0:22:55.44,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-I think that's just you, Hammond. -It's just me, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.47,0:22:57.44,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Here's the moment I think you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.50,0:23:00.54,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,You're driving up a motorway. There's a train track next to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.61,0:23:03.04,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,A train comes. It could be one of those fast ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.11,0:23:06.35,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,The day when you don't try and race the train,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.45,0:23:07.68,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,that's the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.75,0:23:09.52,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-Yes. -I have to race the train.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.58,0:23:11.49,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I have to go faster than the train
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.55,0:23:13.29,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,so everyone on the train looks at me and goes,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.35,0:23:14.96,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,"I've made the wrong travel choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.02,0:23:17.06,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,"I should have gone in the car. It's quicker."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.12,0:23:20.19,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,If you're ever on a train and you look out of the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.26,0:23:23.00,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,you're overtaking me and I can't be bothered to race you,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.06,0:23:27.63,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,it's because I'm on my way to the new Dutch death clinic.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.70,0:23:28.67,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,And that is the end of Conversation Street.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.74,0:23:30.64,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Now, if you have children,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.70,0:23:33.51,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,there's every chance they'll spend every spare second they have
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.57,0:23:35.01,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,playing Zombie Splatter 7 ,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.08,0:23:37.21,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,or some other such computer game,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.28,0:23:40.11,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,but what about more traditional board games?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.18,0:23:43.62,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Kids these days say they're not interested in such games,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.68,0:23:47.25,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,but I believe they would be if they were bigger
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.32,0:23:49.16,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,and involved cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.29,0:23:53.89,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,To prove our point,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.96,0:23:57.50,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,we've come here, to the countryside.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.53,0:24:01.40,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,And on the board-game front,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.50,0:24:03.27,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,we shall start with a classic.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.34,0:24:06.81,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,A game where two players try and guess where each other's ships are,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.87,0:24:10.04,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,and then blow them up by firing missiles at them.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.11,0:24:11.31,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,It's a simple game,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.38,0:24:14.31,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,and, as such, if you want to play it with cars,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.38,0:24:15.95,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,you don't need much.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.28,0:24:20.52,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,In fact, all you need
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.59,0:24:23.26,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,is a massive former Cold War airfield
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.32,0:24:27.63,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,with enough tarmac to accommodate the board for your board game.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.93,0:24:32.30,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,With a big enough slab of airfield,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.37,0:24:33.97,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,you can then lay out your grid,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.03,0:24:36.54,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,onto which you can place your battleships.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.60,0:24:38.07,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,And all you need for that
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.14,0:24:41.24,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,is several thousand pounds' worth of old cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.61,0:24:44.61,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,But not any old cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.68,0:24:46.31,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,This stretch limo, for example,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.38,0:24:50.05,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,may have seen active service on hundreds of hen nights,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.12,0:24:54.09,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,but it makes the perfect aircraft carrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.15,0:24:56.06,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,And then there's this Toyota Prius.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.12,0:24:59.06,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Its electric engine makes it perfect as a submarine,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.13,0:25:00.63,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,silent running.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.69,0:25:04.06,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,And then there's this Chrysler PT Cruiser convertible.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.13,0:25:06.83,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,There is no naval equivalent for this car,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.90,0:25:08.27,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,but who cares if we blow it up?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.33,0:25:10.57,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Because it is, after all, crap.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.57,0:25:16.44,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,And speaking of blowing up, we now come to the missiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.58,0:25:21.15,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,For these, you need a car that is frightening and lethal.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.21,0:25:25.65,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,A car that strikes fear into other motorists.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.72,0:25:28.45,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,And what better car could there be for this job
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.59,0:25:30.79,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,than the magnificent G-Wiz?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.99,0:25:34.43,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,All I needed now was an opponent,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.49,0:25:36.20,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,a board-game veteran,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.26,0:25:39.13,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,a man who thinks Call Of Duty
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.20,0:25:41.30,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,is a visit to the lavatory.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.37,0:25:43.97,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,That's excellent, Hammond. You've thought of everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.04,0:25:46.61,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I know, I have. Containers as the fence.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.64,0:25:48.84,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,A fireman, in case things get out of hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.91,0:25:51.68,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,A health-and-safety bloke to stop us blowing ourselves up.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.75,0:25:54.88,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Cars that look exactly like ships. The lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.95,0:25:57.12,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,But how will you fire the missiles at the cars?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.18,0:26:01.66,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, that is the real genius in my plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.72,0:26:03.99,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Easy, powerful and proven.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.06,0:26:06.89,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Fire the G-Wiz missiles with the movie cannon.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.96,0:26:09.96,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-You reckon that's accurate enough? -Well, it's a cannon.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.03,0:26:11.90,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,But you've got to hit a specific square.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.97,0:26:15.70,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,You aim the cannon. You adjust the trajectory and the elevation.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.77,0:26:18.64,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-You can work that out? -It's a cannon.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.64,0:26:21.78,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,To shut James up, I took one of the spare cars
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.84,0:26:23.94,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,to demonstrate a practice shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.28,0:26:26.91,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Right, we're all set.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.98,0:26:29.35,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,It's fully charged. Pressure's good. Fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.83,0:26:43.33,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,JAMES: I had a better idea for the weapons-launching system.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.68,0:26:59.15,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,So, there you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.21,0:27:01.55,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,You call out the grid reference that you want,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.68,0:27:04.92,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,and the driver just manoeuvres the jib exactly over that square,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.99,0:27:06.69,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,and then drops the G-Wiz missile.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.69,0:27:09.32,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,It is absolutely unerringly accurate.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.39,0:27:10.96,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.02,0:27:14.73,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Unlike everything else I've done here, with all this stuff,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.80,0:27:18.97,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,this is all things you can do at home in your garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.03,0:27:21.00,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,RICHARD: With the giant containers
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.07,0:27:26.17,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,making sure neither of us could see what the other was doing,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.24,0:27:30.41,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,...James and I moved our battleships into place.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.41,0:27:36.78,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,And with the board laid out, it was time to play.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.85,0:27:40.15,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Right, the hen-night limos each require two hits to be sunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.22,0:27:44.09,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Both the motorhomes, they each require two hits to be sunk as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.16,0:27:46.93,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,And then my Prius and your PT Cruiser,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.99,0:27:49.10,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,they each require one to be sunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.16,0:27:51.77,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,We've got ten G-Wiz missiles each.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.83,0:27:53.97,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Five hits needed to win. Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.84,0:27:56.54,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.60,0:28:00.24,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Having won the toss, James would be first to fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.31,0:28:03.38,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,but I had a cunning plan to thwart him.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.44,0:28:07.95,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,What I've done is put a couple of my ships right out on the edges,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.01,0:28:11.45,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,because James will think, "Hammond's a bit thick,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.52,0:28:14.79,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,and it's a typically amateurish tactic to put your ships on the edge,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.86,0:28:16.12,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,so that's what he'll have done."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.19,0:28:18.12,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,But then he'll think, "Hang on.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.19,0:28:20.13,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Even Hammond's not that thick.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.19,0:28:22.33,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,He just wants me to think he's thick,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.40,0:28:25.00,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,so he'll have put his cars in the middle."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.07,0:28:27.63,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,James will then not go for the edges,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.77,0:28:29.27,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,he'll go for the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.34,0:28:32.07,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,But my ships will be at the edges.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.14,0:28:35.68,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,It's like a... double, or even a triple bluff.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.78,0:28:37.34,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Now, Hammond is a bit thick, really,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.41,0:28:40.41,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,so I reckon he'll have put his all around the edges.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.65,0:28:44.89,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,D2, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.22,0:28:49.36,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.93,0:29:03.80,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-What was that? -It was my limo.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.84,0:29:07.14,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Hit on your limo on D2, thank you. Your shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.11,0:29:14.68,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Red crane driver, I'd like C4, please. C4.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.82,0:29:16.05,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.82,0:29:25.66,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,That's a miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.73,0:29:28.59,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,C4, miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.66,0:29:30.16,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Back to my original theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.23,0:29:31.56,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Hammond will have gone along the edge,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.63,0:29:32.83,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm pretty confident in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.90,0:29:35.50,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,So is it there, or is it there?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.57,0:29:40.14,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Green crane driver, fire at D1.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.21,0:29:41.34,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.88,0:29:51.62,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-Yes! -You sank my limousine!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.68,0:29:57.39,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,One sinking to me, a miss for Admiral Hammond.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.46,0:30:00.03,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,And you've overdone the explosives.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.30,0:30:04.36,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,One plan would be, if you're playing this at home,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.43,0:30:07.30,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,do it on a day when there's a lot of barbecues in the area.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.37,0:30:09.37,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,That way, people will just think, "Well, yeah,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.44,0:30:12.24,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,it's a big barbecue they're having next door."
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.64,0:30:15.51,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,RICHARD: With my aircraft carrier gone
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.58,0:30:20.18,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,and James's fleet unscathed, I had to break my duck.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.25,0:30:23.15,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I'd like you to hit B2, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.52,0:30:27.89,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.95,0:30:29.36,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,B2. Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.42,0:30:31.42,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, there's no... Where are they?!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.49,0:30:32.79,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I've just got a feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.86,0:30:35.90,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,B1. B1, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.34,0:30:46.47,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Red crane driver, can I have square A1?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.91,0:30:50.41,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.72,0:30:57.42,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes! Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.48,0:31:00.82,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, you are on the run! That is it! Want to give up?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.89,0:31:03.12,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,You've sunk my Cruiser.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.19,0:31:08.03,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,So that's a big red kill on A1. Boom!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.09,0:31:11.03,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,But James wasn't taking this lying down.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.67,0:31:15.44,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,C3. Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.41,0:31:20.51,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.57,0:31:21.57,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,You hit my submarine,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.64,0:31:23.94,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,my invisible, silent-running Prius.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.28,0:31:28.21,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,RICHARD: I am losing badly.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.28,0:31:30.98,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I've scored only one hit, he's scored three.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.25,0:31:34.32,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,But then the game started to turn,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.39,0:31:37.76,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,as James had a run of three straight misses.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.82,0:31:39.19,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,JAMES: Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.83,0:31:49.54,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,It was a miss! Ha-ha!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.60,0:31:52.01,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Thank you. I'm closing down my options.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.07,0:31:56.81,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,It would close your options down further if you were to hit rather than miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.88,0:32:00.68,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Which was exactly what I was now doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.75,0:32:01.98,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,B3, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.49,0:32:07.22,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,A3, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.52,0:32:12.79,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.86,0:32:15.33,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,You've sunk my battleship.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.40,0:32:17.56,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I am raining down destruction
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.63,0:32:20.17,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,on your dwindling fleet of doomed ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.23,0:32:21.67,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,You loser. Ha-ha!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.73,0:32:24.50,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,No, I'm not losing. We're neck and neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.71,0:32:28.11,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Annoyingly, James was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.17,0:32:30.68,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I still had my battleship Winnebago,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.74,0:32:33.85,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,and he still had his stretched aircraft carrier,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.91,0:32:37.68,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,both of which needed two hits to destroy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.75,0:32:39.49,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,It was May's turn to play.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.02,0:32:43.39,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,B2.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.46,0:32:46.03,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,RICHARD: Critical stage of the game now.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.03,0:32:47.73,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,A hit now and I'm in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.93,0:32:50.33,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.80,0:32:58.24,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes! Yes! Yes! Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.30,0:33:01.57,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,It shouldn't feel so good, but it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.68,0:33:04.28,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.05,0:33:09.35,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,It's gonna be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.42,0:33:12.52,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Red crane, target C1, please. C1.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.62,0:33:15.62,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.06,0:33:21.53,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Hard luck, Horatio Hammond.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.96,0:33:25.77,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,All I've got to do now,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.83,0:33:27.77,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,get inside Richard Hammond's mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.83,0:33:31.94,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,An awful place, admittedly, but if I can just get in there for a second,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.07,0:33:33.74,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,which way has he put it?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.81,0:33:36.34,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,There and there; there and there; there and there?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.92,0:33:44.25,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,C2.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.09,0:33:50.36,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.36,0:33:58.56,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,That'll be a miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.70,0:34:05.47,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,That, Captain May, was a miss!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.47,0:34:13.25,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,However, while James now had to choose between just two squares,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.31,0:34:15.78,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I was looking at a choice of six.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.15,0:34:20.29,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Red crane, target C2, please. C2.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.23,0:34:28.13,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Red crane, fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.16,0:34:29.70,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I meant C3! I meant...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.57,0:34:35.77,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.84,0:34:39.14,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes! Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.21,0:34:41.67,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Bollocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.74,0:34:45.81,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,RICHARD: That mistaken shot wasn't just a hit,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.88,0:34:47.95,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,it had changed everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.01,0:34:50.78,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Because I said C2, when actually I meant three,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.85,0:34:52.72,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,in case it was there,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.79,0:34:54.22,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,that's a kill - bang -
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.29,0:34:55.86,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,which means it has to be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.92,0:34:58.26,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,It can't be here or here, so I've got him.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.32,0:35:00.29,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,James, you do know what that means, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.36,0:35:01.93,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes, I've just worked it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.99,0:35:04.53,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I've got to get this right, otherwise you've won.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.60,0:35:08.60,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-Do you want to surrender? -No, I don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.67,0:35:11.50,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,JAMES: So, I was now faced with the choice
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.57,0:35:13.74,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,that would decide the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.18,0:35:18.64,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,A2 or B3?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.71,0:35:21.51,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,A2, B3. What would Richard Hammond do?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.28,0:35:25.55,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Green-crane driver...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.69,0:35:30.89,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.30,0:35:37.83,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Come on, you bewildered old spaniel - miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.23,0:35:42.44,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Right. Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.22,0:36:05.56,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, God!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.23,0:36:11.43,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Hammond!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.23,0:36:15.37,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,RICHARD: Best of three?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.87,0:36:21.14,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,JEREMY: I bet...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.24,0:36:24.34,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I bet the makers of Sony PlayStation are quaking in their boots.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.41,0:36:26.01,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, I wouldn't be surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.08,0:36:28.51,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-They will go, "Oh, my..." -I know. There's the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.58,0:36:31.68,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-That was a total waste of time. -Well, now, hang on.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.75,0:36:35.39,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,No, we destroyed a PT Cruiser, a Prius and many G-Wizs.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.46,0:36:37.72,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, that's true, yes. But James...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.79,0:36:39.16,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,James?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.06,0:36:46.47,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Never mind. Let's move on to Celebrity Brain Crash.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.78,0:36:58.51,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,This week...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.58,0:37:01.65,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,This week, we don't just have one star,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.71,0:37:03.48,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,we have several.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.55,0:37:05.35,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,They're one of the biggest bands
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.42,0:37:07.39,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,ever to come out of Holland,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.45,0:37:08.65,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,and they're going to begin here,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.72,0:37:13.29,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,in the sixth largest port in the world...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.29,0:37:14.79,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,by performing their biggest hit,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.86,0:37:17.36,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,by which I mean... their hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.43,0:37:20.13,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Ladies and gentlemen, Golden Earring!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.30,0:37:23.40,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,RICHARD: And there they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.47,0:37:24.80,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I tell you what,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.87,0:37:26.87,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,we ought to make the lights go a bit better.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.94,0:37:29.84,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Can we dim the lights? That's better. A bit more rock 'n' roll.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.91,0:37:31.08,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,What is their hit?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.14,0:37:34.21,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, this is Holland, birthplace of the speed camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.31,0:37:36.05,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,It's obvious. Radar Love.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.92,0:37:44.02,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,d I've been drivin' all night My hands wet on the wheel d
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.33,0:37:51.70,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,RICHARD: Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.90,0:37:55.84,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,JEREMY: OK, ladies and gentlemen, erm...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.90,0:37:59.34,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,...there's a cable's gone into the sea here, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.34,0:38:01.91,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,...Golden Earring have been electrocuted.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.58,0:38:05.41,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Does that mean they're not coming on, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.48,0:38:08.81,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, James, they've been subjected to a lethal dose of electricity
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.88,0:38:11.82,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,and are now lying on the ground, sizzling, so it's no.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.88,0:38:13.95,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-They're not, no. -OK, OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.02,0:38:16.92,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,That is a very grisly scene. I apologise for that, everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.99,0:38:19.02,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Erm... Probably not as grisly, though,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.09,0:38:22.06,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,as if you're looking at us from out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.13,0:38:23.76,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-Eh? -Well, think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.26,0:38:27.10,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-Oh, yeah! -Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.17,0:38:29.90,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,We are standing in a window in a Dutch port,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.97,0:38:31.04,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,bathed in red light...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.44,0:38:34.14,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,...and we've got no trade lining up.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.21,0:38:35.51,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-Nobody's here. -No.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.58,0:38:37.74,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,No, I know! I know! I've had an idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.81,0:38:40.75,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I've had an idea of how we can fill the time
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.81,0:38:43.25,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,that would have been taken up by the late Golden Earring.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.38,0:38:45.02,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,You see, the thing is...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.08,0:38:47.75,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Can we make the lights go white again now? Pretend that never happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.82,0:38:49.96,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Good. See, the thing is that, in Holland,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.02,0:38:52.73,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,there are these motorist accessory stores, OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.79,0:38:55.16,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-Oh, yeah. -They're open all night. The place is full.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.23,0:38:58.50,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,We went to one last night and bought a load of amazing stuff
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.56,0:39:01.13,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,you can use on the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.20,0:39:03.44,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Bring it over here. Let's show you a couple of things,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.50,0:39:04.54,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,I mean, this, for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.60,0:39:06.07,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,It's an incredible safety device.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.67,0:39:11.41,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,This is very clever, because in a lot of car crashes,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.41,0:39:13.65,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,people bite their tongues, sometimes off.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.71,0:39:16.48,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,But by wearing this neat safety device,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.55,0:39:17.85,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,no way is he biting his tongue.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.92,0:39:19.79,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Look at that! Perfectly safe. That is clever.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.85,0:39:21.62,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Unbelievable. And then you can get traffic cones
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.69,0:39:23.76,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,that fit in the glovebox.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.82,0:39:25.46,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-This is one here.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.03,0:39:29.50,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,RICHARD: Yeah. -It's not funny stuff, this is safety material.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.56,0:39:33.10,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-Another one. -These are compact, so you can fit them in your boot.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.17,0:39:35.70,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,The thing is, though, OK, in America,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.77,0:39:38.54,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,as I'm sure you know, there are high-occupancy vehicle lanes.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.60,0:39:41.17,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,Er... You're not allowed to go in them
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.24,0:39:43.71,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,unless you've got two or more people in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.78,0:39:45.45,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,We've always been very worried in Europe
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.45,0:39:47.45,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,that this idea is gonna come over here,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.51,0:39:49.75,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,but the Dutch have it covered,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.82,0:39:52.65,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,because in these motorist accessory shops,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.72,0:39:54.59,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,you can buy inflatable people.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.65,0:39:56.19,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-We've got one here.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.26,0:39:58.29,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,-Very clever, this. Very clever. -Isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.36,0:40:01.26,字幕ENG,,0,0,0,,The only slight issue is they do take a lot of effort to blow up.
